</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="696" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="5.[1431,2635,275,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1432,1785,275,304]" pageId="5" pageNumber="696">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Deficient" authorityName="Deficient" box="[1981,2187,275,304]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Data" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="696" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Data Deficient</taxonomicName>
on The IUCN Red List. There is little information about population status, ecology, and distribution of Shortridge’s Long-fingered Bat, and additional research is needed to assess its conservation status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
